Package model.team.repository

Interface TeamRepository

All Known Implementing Classes:
SqliteTeamRepository
public interface TeamRepository
TeamRepository specifies the methods required from any class implementing database access for team-related updates, insertions, deletions and queries.
Author:
Bori Fazakas

  • Method Details

    • saveTeam

      int saveTeam​(Team.SavableTeam team) throws java.sql.SQLException, InexistentDatabaseEntityException
      Saves the new team in the database and returns the id of the team in the database. It also sets the id of the team object.
      Parameters:
      team - holds the data of the new team to be saved. The id of team should be null.
      Returns:
      the id of the newly saved team.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.
      InexistentDatabaseEntityException

    • deleteTeam

      void deleteTeam​(int teamId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Deletes the team with the specified id from the database. It also deletes all the memberships related to it. Requirement: all projects and members having foreign keys to teams must already be deleted.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team to delete.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • deleteAllMembersOfTeam

      void deleteAllMembersOfTeam​(int teamId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Deletes all members of the team with id teamId.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team whose members are deleted.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • getTeam

      java.util.Optional<Team> getTeam​(java.lang.String code) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Returns the Team with the specified code from the database, if it exists, wrapped in an Optional.
      Parameters:
      code - is the code of the searched team.
      Returns:
      the team with the given code, or null if it doesn't exist.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the searched team.
      Returns:
      the team with the given code, or null if it doesn't exist.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • getTeamsOfUser

      java.util.List<Team> getTeamsOfUser​(int userId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Searches for and returns all the teams in which the user is a member.
      Parameters:
      userId - is the id of the user whose teams are listed.
      Returns:
      the list of teams in which the user is a member.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • addTeamMember

      void addTeamMember​(int teamId, int userId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Adds user to the members of the team with id teamID
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team which user wants to join. Requirement: The team must exist in the database.
      userId - is the new member's id. Requirement: the user must exist in the database.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • removeTeamMember

      void removeTeamMember​(int teamId, int userId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Removes user from the members of the team with id teamID, if the user was a member previously. Otherwise nothing happens.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team which user wants to leave.
      userId - is the member's id who leaves the team.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • isMemberOfTeam

      boolean isMemberOfTeam​(int teamId, int userId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Chekcs whether a particular user is the member of a particular team.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team.
      userId - is the id of the user whose membership is checked.
      Returns:
      true if and only if the user with userId is member of team with teamId.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • setNewCode

      void setNewCode​(int teamId, java.lang.String newCode) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Sets the new code for the specified team, if it exists.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team to update.
      newCode - is the new code to set.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • setNewManagerPosition

      void setNewManagerPosition​(int teamId, int managerId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Sets the manager of a team to be another existing user, if the team exists. The existence of the user with managerId is not checked.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team which gets a new manager.
      managerId - is the id of the new manager. REMARK: It must exist in the database.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • setNewName

      void setNewName​(int teamId, java.lang.String newTeamName) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Change the name of the team with the given id to the new name.
      Parameters:
      teamId - is the id of the team which gets a new team.
      newTeamName - is the new name of the team.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if the operation could not be performed in the database.

    • getMembersOfTeam

      java.util.List<User> getMembersOfTeam​(int teamId) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Returns the members of the given team.
      Parameters:
      teamId - specifies the team
      Returns:
      a list of members
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - if an error occurs during processing the data in the database
